<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 2:18PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Floyd,
southeastern Walker, western Gordon and northeastern Chattooga
Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 218 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Everett Springs, or 10
miles west of Calhoun, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Calhoun, Summerville, Oostanaula, Subligna, Sugar Valley, Tidings,
Everett Springs, Lake Marvin and James H. Floyd State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
